#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "User Profile"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In {project_name} a user is associated with a set of attributes. These "
"attributes are used to better describe and identify users within "
"{project_name} as well as to pass over additional information to "
"applications about them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"A user profile defines a well-defined schema for representing user "
"attributes and how they are managed within a realm. By providing a "
"consistent view over user information, it allows administrators to control "
"the different aspects on how attributes are managed as well as to make a lot "
"easier to extend {project_name} to support additional attributes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Among other capabilities, user profile enables administrators to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Define a schema for user attributes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Define whether an attribute is required based on contextual information (e."
"g.: if required only for users, or admins, or both, or depending on the "
"scope being requested.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Define specific permissions for viewing and editing user attributes, making "
"possible to adhere to strong privacy requirements where some attributes can "
"not be seen or be changed by third-parties (including administrators)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Dynamically enforce user profile compliance so that user information is "
"always updated and in compliance with the metadata and rules associated with "
"attributes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Define validation rules on a per-attribute basis by leveraging the built-in "
"validators or writing custom ones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The User Profile capabilities are backed by the User Profile SPI. By "
"default, there are two providers you can choose from:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Legacy User Profile Provider (`legacy-user-profile`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Declarative User Profile Provider (`declarative-user-profile`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The legacy provider is enabled by default, and it provides a basic user "
"profile configuration based on the user root attributes such as e-mail, "
"first and last names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"On the other hand, the declarative provider gives you a lot more flexibility "
"to define the user profile configuration to a realm through the "
"administration console and a well-defined JSON schema."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In the next sections, we'll be looking at how to use the declarative "
"provider to define your own user profile configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
msgid ""
"In the future, the `declarative-user-profile` provider is going to replace "
"the legacy provider and become the default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling the Declarative User Profile"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In addition to enabling the `declarative_user_profile` feature, you should "
"use the link:{installguide_link}#_start_cli[CLI] to set the `declarative-"
"user-profile` provider as the default provider as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ /subsystem=keycloak-server/spi=userProfile:add(default-provider=declarative-user-profile)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "After setting the default provider, make sure to restart the server."
msgstr ""

